<ptxt>Using a hammer, tap the yoke until there is no clearance between the spider bearings and snap rings.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="G022297E06" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Align the matchmarks on the yoke and shaft.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Install 2 spider bearings on the shaft side.</ptxt>
<ptxt>Install the other universal joint spider(s) using the same procedures.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM000000ZZ5025X_01_0002" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000046H00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT UNIVERSAL JOINT SPIDER ASSEMBLY</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Check the spider bearings for wear or damage.</ptxt>
<ptxt>If any of the bearings is worn or damaged, replace it.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Check each spider bearing's axial play by turning the yoke while holding the shaft tightly.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Maximum bearing axial play</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>0.05 mm (0.00197 in.)</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the bearing axial play is more than the maximum, replace the spider bearing.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM000000ZZ5025X_01_0003" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000046I00000">
<ptxt>INSTALL CENTER NO. 1 SUPPORT BEARING ASSEMBLY</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Install the center support bearing to the intermediate shaft.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C115788E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Coat the splines of the intermediate shaft with MP grease.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="F049874E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Align the matchmarks on the flange coupling and intermediate shaft, and install the flange coupling to the intermediate shaft.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Install the washer.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using SST to hold the flange coupling, press the bearing into position by installing a new lock nut.</ptxt>
<sst>
<sstitem>
<s-number>09330-00021</s-number>
</sstitem>
</sst>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="F049875E02" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<torque>
<torqueitem>
<t-value1>181</t-value1>
<t-value2>1850</t-value2>
<t-value4>134</t-value4>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Loosen the lock nut.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Tighten the lock nut again.</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem>
<t-value1>68</t-value1>
<t-value2>700</t-value2>
<t-value4>51</t-value4>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Using a chisel and hammer, stake the lock nut.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C061391E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Align the matchmarks on the flange yoke and flange coupling, and connect them with the 4 washers and 4 nuts.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="F049877E01" width="2.775699831in" height="1.771723296in"/>
</figure>
<torque>
<torqueitem>
<t-value1>88</t-value1>
<t-value2>897</t-value2>
<t-value4>65</t-value4>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<atten4>
<ptxt>If any parts with matchmarks is replaced during inspection, reassemble them so that the yoke of the intermediate shaft and the rear flange yoke of the propeller shaft are at right angles to each other.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
<s-1 id="RM000000ZZ5025X_01_0004" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__000046J00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT PROPELLER WITH CENTER BEARING SHAFT ASSEMBLY</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>When the spider bearing is replaced, be sure that the grease fitting holes are facing the direction shown in the illustration. </ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C191269E01" width="7.106578999in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
</s2>
</content1>
